  "prompt": "Why is honey commonly packaged in bear bottles?",
  "response": "The bear-shaped bottle for honey is primarily a marketing design created by the Dutch Gold Honey company in 1957. The cute, recognizable shape was intended to make the product more appealing to consumers, especially children. It's not related to bears actually collecting honey in the wild, though bears are known to eat honey from beehives. The unique packaging has become an iconic and popular way to sell honey, making it stand out on store shelves.",
